Qd2 {Preparing 0-0-0. Obviously White wants to create a position with chances
to make an attack.} c6 6. f4 {The indirect pressure that the bishop places on
e,7 plus the threat of playing e5, determines White's advantage.} O-O 7. Nf3 {
Developing with maximum activity.} Bg4 {This move is not very accurate - the
bishop is not doing very much on g4; better is d5 or b5.} (7... d5) 8. Bd3 Nbd7
9. e5 $1 {White seizes the initiative with this move.} dxe5 10. fxe5 Nd5 11.
