Nb6 13. Kb1 $14) 11... Nxc3 12. Qxc3 c5 13. Bb5 {Black's position is under
terrible pressure: the two bishops and the d1 rook.} (13. dxc5 {Was probably a
slightly more accurate choice. White's position is better!} Bxf3 14. gxf3 Nxe5
15. Be2 $14) 13... f6 $4 (13... a6 {Was much better - and Black is close to
equality.}) 14. dxc5 $1 {Opening the 'd' file and threatening Qc4+. White has
a decisive advantage.} Kh8 15. exf6 exf6 16. Bf4 a6 17. Ba4 b5 18. cxb6 Rc8 19.
